  "text": "In robotics, walking has historically been treated separately from manipulation. However, manipulation and locomotion must be consistent, in particular during collaborative carrying. Eventually, both need to be thought of as parts of the whole-body control problem (discussed in Section IV-A). In this section, we revisit the modeling of WPGs, and redesign them with physical collaboration in mind. This section was partially published in [CITATION_1] . Here, we recall the main points, namely the addition of the external wrench into the model, and the design of objectives and constraints, based on this wrench. Additionally, we better specify the usage of our new WPG in the collaborative carrying task.",
